# VRoid material names

## Phase B cleanup (strip prefix + Instance)

| Pattern removed | Example |
|-----------------|---------|
| `N\d{2}_\d{3}_\d{2}_` | `N00_005_01_`, `N00_001_02_` |
| `N\d{2}_\d{3}_[A-Za-z]+_\d{2}_` | `N00_000_Hair_00_` |
| trailing ` (Instance)` | outline mats: inner name only |

## Skin materials

VRoid **source** name is unchanged on import. Phase B **workflow** rename:

| Source (VRoid import) | Workflow name |
|-----------------------|---------------|
| `N00_000_00_Face_00_SKIN (Instance)` | `Face_Skin` |
| `N00_000_00_Body_00_SKIN (Instance)` | `Body_Skin` |

Use **`Face_Skin`** / **`Body_Skin`** in pipeline scripts. `resolve_material_by_token("Face_Skin")` still matches the source datablock before Phase B runs.

## Clothing naming (keep tail + layer suffix)

| Import | After Phase B | Meaning |
|--------|---------------|---------|
| `N00_005_01_Tops_01_CLOTH (Instance)` | `Hoodie` |
| `N00_005_01_Tops_01_CLOTH_01 (Instance)` | `Hoodie_01` |
| `N00_005_01_Tops_01_CLOTH_02 (Instance)` | `Hoodie_02` |
| `N00_001_02_*_CLOTH (Instance)` | `*_CLOTH` | Uniform **vest** slot |

VRoid tail `Tops_01_CLOTH` (+ optional `_01`, `_02` layers) → **`Hoodie`**, **`Hoodie_01`**, **`Hoodie_02`**. Alias map keeps import + VRoid tail names for lookup.

## Alias map (match pre- and post-cleanup)

Phase B stores `scene["vroid_material_rename_map"]` (`import_name` → `cleaned_name`).

When matching materials (tri-to-quad extraction, MToon sync, mesh-by-slot):

1. Use `resolve_material_by_token(token)` from `skills/vroid-vrm-blender-cleanup/tools/clean_vroid_material_names.py`
2. Or `material_name_variants(token)` to test both import and cleaned names
3. Prefer tokens like `Hoodie`, `Hoodie_01`, `Face_Skin` — `resolve_material_by_token()` also accepts VRoid import / tail names via alias map

Do not assume materials still carry `N00_*` after Phase B has run.
